{% extends "base.html.twig" %}

{% block title %}NorthOps — AI Systems Architecture{% endblock %}
{% block description %}We design and build AI-native systems for scaleups and public-sector teams. Spec-driven development, multi-agent orchestration, deterministic pipelines.{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="section section-hero">
        <div class="container">
            <h1>AI systems architecture.<br>Shipped by the people who designed it.</h1>
            <p class="hero-sub">
                We design and build AI-native systems for scaleups and public-sector teams.
                Spec-driven development, multi-agent orchestration, deterministic pipelines.
                We run in production, not in prototypes.
            </p>
            <div class="hero-ctas">
                <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Book a discovery call</a>
                <a href="#case-studies" class="btn btn-secondary btn-lg">See our work →</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Service Grid -->
    <section class="section">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="service-grid">
                <a href="/services/ai-systems-architecture" class="service-card">
                    <h3>AI Systems Architecture</h3>
                    <p>Architecture, specs, and deterministic patterns for teams adopting LLMs, agentic workflows, or AI-assisted development at scale.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="/services/platform-engineering" class="service-card">
                    <h3>Platform Engineering</h3>
                    <p>Production systems on Laravel, Symfony, or modern TypeScript stacks. Entity-first architecture, observability, CI/CD, agent-safe repos.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="/services/content-data-pipelines" class="service-card">
                    <h3>Content &amp; Data Pipelines</h3>
                    <p>Automated ingestion, transformation, and delivery pipelines that move your data where it needs to go. Reliably and on schedule.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="/services/advisory-fractional-leadership" class="service-card">
                    <h3>Advisory &amp; Fractional Leadership</h3>
                    <p>Senior judgment on retainer. Embedded in your architecture decisions, roadmap reviews, and hiring calls — one or two days a week.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="/services/indigenous-data-sovereignty" class="service-card">
                    <h3>Indigenous Data Sovereignty</h3>
                    <p>Systems that respect OCAP® principles and community data sovereignty. Led by an Anishinaabe operator from Sagamok First Nation.</p>
                </a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Case Studies -->
    <section id="case-studies" class="section section-alt">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Selected work</h2>
            <div class="case-grid">
                <article class="case-card">
                    <h3>Waaseyaa Framework</h3>
                    <p class="case-meta">Entity-first, AI-native PHP framework</p>
                    <p>Teams adopting AI-assisted development need a codebase that agents can reason about safely. We built Waaseyaa on Symfony 7 with entity-first architecture, 40+ split packages across 7 architectural layers, and codified context rules that keep AI output aligned with project conventions. Powers real production deployments including OIATC.</p>
                    <p><a href="https://github.com/waaseyaa" target="_blank" rel="noopener">github.com/waaseyaa →</a></p>
                </article>
                <article class="case-card">
                    <h3>OIATC</h3>
                    <p class="case-meta">Ontario Indigenous AI &amp; Technology Council</p>
                    <p>A production website for a council advancing Indigenous participation in AI and technology. Built on Waaseyaa to demonstrate the framework's fit for public-sector and Indigenous-led organizations. Delivered content management, programs, events, and member-facing features with an agent-safe codebase the council's technical partners can extend.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="case-card">
                    <h3>jonesrussell/skills</h3>
                    <p class="case-meta">Reusable AI skill library</p>
                    <p>A published library of AI skill templates covering code review, codebase analysis, spec-driven development, and domain-specific workflows. Used internally on every engagement; published openly so clients can audit and extend. Demonstrates how to scale senior judgment across an AI-augmented development practice.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="case-card">
                    <h3>Claudriel</h3>
                    <p class="case-meta">AI personal operations system</p>
                    <p>An AI operations layer for developer workflow — multi-agent orchestration, structured memory, and spec-driven task execution across a portfolio of projects. Shows the operator-tooling lane: what happens when you take AI-native patterns past individual features and into the daily practice of a senior engineer.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="case-card">
                    <h3>North Cloud / Newsy</h3>
                    <p class="case-meta">Content intelligence platform (Go + Rust)</p>
                    <p>Vertical-specific news aggregators backed by a crawler, classifier, and publisher pipeline in Go and Rust. Real-time ingestion, AI-assisted classification, and deterministic routing to downstream channels. Demonstrates what our pipeline and AI engineering look like at platform scale.</p>
                </article>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Why NorthOps / Proof Points -->
    <section class="section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Why NorthOps</h2>
            <div class="proof-grid">
                <div class="proof-point">
                    <h3>Senior-only every time</h3>
                    <p>Every engagement is led by senior engineers with 10+ years of experience. No handoffs to juniors, no bait-and-switch.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="proof-point">
                    <h3>AI-native from the ground up</h3>
                    <p>Spec-driven development, agent-safe repos, and codified context — AI isn't a bolt-on for us. It's how we work, and how we build for clients.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="proof-point">
                    <h3>Full-stack coverage</h3>
                    <p>Backend, frontend, infrastructure, and AI. Engineers who work across the entire stack daily.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="proof-point">
                    <h3>Indigenous-led</h3>
                    <p>Anishinaabe operator from Sagamok First Nation. We bring lived experience to data-sovereignty conversations and Indigenous procurement.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="proof-point">
                    <h3>No overhead tax</h3>
                    <p>No project managers, no account executives, no layers between you and the people writing the code. You talk directly to the engineers.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Process Steps -->
    <section class="section section-alt">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>How it works</h2>
            <div class="process-steps">
                <div class="process-step">
                    <span class="step-number">1</span>
                    <h3>Discovery call</h3>
                    <p>A free 15–30 minute conversation to understand your project, constraints, and goals. No commitment, no pitch.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="process-step">
                    <span class="step-number">2</span>
                    <h3>Shape the engagement</h3>
                    <p>Discovery sprint, fixed-price MVP, implementation contract, or fractional retainer. We match the shape to the work, not the other way around.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="process-step">
                    <span class="step-number">3</span>
                    <h3>SOW + payment</h3>
                    <p>A clear statement of work with transparent pricing. You'll know the deliverables and price before anything starts.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="process-step">
                    <span class="step-number">4</span>
                    <h3>Build</h3>
                    <p>Short, focused sprints with regular progress updates. You'll see working software — and the specs behind it — early and often.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="process-step">
                    <span class="step-number">5</span>
                    <h3>Deliver</h3>
                    <p>Deployed, documented, and handed off. You get source code, deployment guides, and a working system your team can extend without us.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Team -->
    <section class="section">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>The team</h2>
            <div class="team-grid">
                <div class="team-member">
                    <img src="/images/team/russell-jones.jpg" alt="Russell Jones" class="team-photo">
                    <h3>Russell Jones</h3>
                    <p class="team-title">Principal Engineer &amp; Founder</p>
                    <p>AI systems architecture, spec-driven development, and the Waaseyaa framework. Anishinaabe, rooted in Sagamok First Nation, based in Sudbury, Ontario.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="team-member">
                    <img src="/images/team/luc-hebert.jpg" alt="Luc Hebert" class="team-photo">
                    <h3>Luc Hebert</h3>
                    <p class="team-title">Frontend &amp; TypeScript Collaborator</p>
                    <p>Frontend architecture, TypeScript, and AI integrations. Collaborates on NorthOps engagements where interface and LLM-powered workflows intersect.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA Banner -->
    <section class="section section-cta">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Ready to start?</h2>
            <p>Book a free discovery call.</p>
            <a href="https://calendly.com/jonesrussell42" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Book a discovery call</a>
        </div>
    </section>
{% endblock %}
